snippet.textDisplay: To the people who seem to feel the need to shame people for  memorializing Kobe, because they feel the other people who passed aren't getting public attention. I'd keep in mind, those people aren't public figures. We all pray for their families and we pray for their souls. I'm very sure that the family and friends of those people are celebrating them. Just because someone put up a post about Kobe and his daughter does not mean they don't care about the other people. People are allowed to memorialize him, especially if they feel they've been affected by him in some way. We all need to be realistic, Kobe Bryant is an extraordinary person, who has done extraordinary things. He was actually very giving and involved in a lot of different things and there are a lot of people who are inspired by him. He has contributed a lot to the world, so there are people who are going to celebrate him. It is unnecessary for people to go into every post about Kobe or his daughter and feel the need to say why aren't you talkin about the others? This video is  specifically for him and his daughter and that's okay. If you or anyone else want to celebrate the other passengers you can do so as well.  Celebrating Kobe does not de-value the others. Its not a negative thing, people tend to like to bring negativity, when it is clearly unnecessary. He's being celebrated and it's alright to allow that to happen. If you are concerned about the others why don't you do some research on them and post your video. Right now this video is about Kobe and his daughter.

snippet.textDisplay: This was absolutely priceless. Good job Dre. This has taken me out of denial that Kobe is really gone. Looking at him play reminds me of where I was back then. I’m happy now, but those days were awesome. Watching basketball was awesome back then. Soooo many great players and moments. I’m from Chicago but I’ve been a die hard fan of the Lakers way before Kobe. Him and my son share a name. But not on purpose. My son was named before Kobe was entered the game. Always having Positive energy is how I survive in this world. Watching Kobe play through obstacles on and off the court was very inspirational and I thank him for being so many examples. No one is perfect, but his energy was always contagious. Love him or hate him, but you can’t deny him. I would have loved to seen him take GiGi to the top. We need more father daughter role models. That story was cut way too short.

snippet.textDisplay: No matter how many times I watch this it still gives me goosebumps. I’ve been a Lakers fan since the mid-70s...almost my entire life. Our family lost our son a little over 3 years ago. As a parent this pain is unimaginable. The loss is unimaginable. All my prayers go out to Vanessa, the girls, the parents, and siblings. Life will never be the same...starting new “norms” and trying to find peace is all we can pray for. 🙏🏽
